acterized in that the difference between the refractive index at the grain boundary and the refractive index of the main phase of the oxide ceramic crystal at 25&#xb0; C. is 0.004 or less. The present invention is capable of reliably providing a magneto-optical ceramic material for Faraday rotators of optical isolators and the like, said magneto-optical ceramic material having good polarization state and large extinction ratio, and enables size reduction of an optical isolator that is used for fiber laser for processing machines.</p></abstract></us-patent-application>